# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# COMMIT MESSAGE REQUIREMENTS:
# 1. ALL commit messages MUST be detailed and verbose
# 2. Subject line should be clear but concise (max 72 chars)
# 3. Body MUST include comprehensive details:
#    - What changes were made (detailed list)
#    - Why changes were made (motivation)
#    - How it affects the system
#    - Any potential side effects
# 4. Use multiple paragraphs and bullet points for clarity
# 5. Include examples or context where relevant
# 6. Reference related commits, issues, or documentation
#
# Types:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   docs     (documentation changes)
#   style    (formatting, missing semicolons, etc; no code change)
#   refactor (refactoring production code)
#   test     (adding missing tests, refactoring tests)
#   chore    (updating grunt tasks etc; no production code change)
#   content  (adding or updating content like recipes, images, etc)
#
# Scopes:
#   recipes  (recipe-related changes)
#   i18n     (internationalization/translations)
#   auth     (authentication)
#   ui       (user interface)
#   api      (API changes)
#   infra    (infrastructure)
#   deps     (dependencies)
#   ci       (continuous integration)
#   *        (multiple scopes)
#
# Subject should:
#   * use imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
#   * don't capitalize first letter
#   * no dot (.) at the end
#   * be clear and descriptive
#
# Body MUST:
#   * be detailed and comprehensive
#   * include motivation for the change
#   * contrast this with previous behavior
#   * explain technical details where relevant
#   * list all significant changes
#   * mention any related changes or dependencies
#
# Footer should:
#   * reference GitHub/GitLab issues
#   * breaking changes start with BREAKING CHANGE:
#   * mention any follow-up work needed
#
# Examples:
#   feat(recipes): add comprehensive Thai cuisine collection
#   
#   Add 16 authentic Thai recipes across different categories including soups,
#   curries, stir-fries, salads, and desserts. Each recipe includes:
#   
#   - Detailed ingredients with measurements
#   - Step-by-step cooking instructions
#   - Cultural notes and serving suggestions
#   - Spanish translations for all content
#   - Nutritional information
#   - Tips for perfect results
#   - Common variations
#   
#   Technical changes:
#   - Updated recipe schema to support new fields
#   - Enhanced frontmatter handling for translations
#   - Added new recipe categories
#   - Implemented proper YAML formatting
#   
#   Related changes:
#   - Updated recipe index
#   - Added new recipe tags
#   - Enhanced search functionality
#   
#   Testing:
#   - Verified all recipes compile correctly
#   - Checked translations accuracy
#   - Validated nutritional calculations
#   
#   Closes #123, Related to #456
#
#   content(recipes): add detailed Pad Thai recipe with comprehensive instructions
#   
#   Create new Pad Thai recipe with extensive details including:
#   
#   Recipe components:
#   - Authentic ingredient list with substitutions
#   - Detailed prep and cooking instructions
#   - Step-by-step photos
#   - Traditional cooking techniques
#   - Common pitfalls and solutions
#   
#   Documentation:
#   - Added cultural context
#   - Included serving suggestions
#   - Added wine pairing recommendations
#   
#   Technical aspects:
#   - Enhanced recipe schema
#   - Added new ingredient tags
#   - Updated search index
#   
#   Part of Thai cuisine collection #789
